The paper discusses a lightweight environment for reinforcement learning, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of reinforcement learning algorithms to solve tasks in the environment suggests that it could also fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). The fact that the environment emulates physical properties of the real world and involves navigation tasks suggests that it could also fall under the categories of robotics (cs.RO) and systems and control (cs.SY).
